we first thing that we can say is that we have the hight of the square

this is given to us as the quantity r

our next step is to find the width of the rectangle

we then can say that sense the circles are tangent to one another we have a triangle that we can draw form the 2 centers we know this is r + r/2

we then can use the pythagorean theorem to solve fot the other length
$(\frac{3r}{2})^2 = x^2 + (\frac{r}{2})^2$
$(\frac{3r}{2})^2 - (\frac{r}{2})^2 = x^2$
$\sqrt{(\frac{3r}{2})^2 - (\frac{r}{2})^2} = x$

so therefor the area of the rectangle
$r\sqrt{(\frac{3r}{2})^2 - (\frac{r}{2})^2}$
simplified
$=r\sqrt{(\frac{8r^2}{4})}$
$=r\frac{2\sqrt{2}r}{2}$
$=r\sqrt{2}r$
$=\sqrt{2}r^2$

so if the r = 1 then the area is $\sqrt{2}$
